my boyfriend says i have an eating disorder do i i only eat dinner each day and when that time comes i only eat a small portion i just don't like to eat food makes me sick now looking at people eat makes me wanna throw up is that even normal i'm trying to convince him i don't have an eating disorder but he keeps saying i do even if we were competent doctors none of us here could give you a diagnosis over the internet what we can tell you is that what you describe is not normal you might not have an eating disorder it depends on why food makes you sick and why looking at people eating makes you want to throw up start with your family doctor if you don't have one get one or if you are in college go to the health center if there is no physical reason for you body to be acting this way then start seeing a competent therapist i've provided a link to refer to if you decide you may have an eating disorder it will help you find a professional in your state if you live in the usa they have a live helpline that is available live helpline hours monday friday am pm pacific Eating disorder Binge eating disorder Medicine Terri Schiavo Anorexia nervosa Fasting Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Psychiatry Fecal incontinence Physical therapy Gender identity disorder Hypoglycemia Dissociative identity disorder Coeliac disease Autism Super Size Me Osteopathy Insomnia Reparative therapy Stomach cancer Mental Health Act 1983 Chronic fatigue syndrome Disease Sydney Riot of 1879 Psychotherapy Borderline personality disorder Clinical depression Down syndrome Cephalic disorder Nutrition Dieting Psychosis Urinary incontinence Dyspraxia Chiropractic Bipolar disorder Meal Nurse Andreas Grassl Aliens of London Multiple sclerosis Pneumonia National Health Service Crohn's disease Avenue Q Sports medicine Gastroparesis Autism rights movement Obsessive-compulsive disorder Education in the United States Transsexuality Diabetes mellitus Social rule Involuntary commitment Oral sex Prostate cancer LSD Tooth ename